solution.p:
The graph of k(x) = s(x) - 1 is s shifted down 1 unit;
the point (-2, -3) moves to (-2, -4).
The graph of j(x) = s(x-2) is s shifted right 2 units;
the point (-2, -3) moves to (0, -3).
The graph of m(x) = s(x-2) - 1 combines both — a shift right 2 units
and down 1 unit — moving (-2, -3) to (0, -4).
